-- Embraer Drops After Goldman Cuts Stock From Buy: Sao Paulo Mover
-- B y   J o s e   S e r g i o   O s s e
-- 2012-04-20T20:50:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-20/embraer-drops-after-goldman-cuts-stock-from-buy-sao-paulo-mover.html
Embraer SA (EMBR3) , the world’s fourth-
biggest aircraft maker, fell the most in more than six weeks
after Goldman Sachs Group Inc. cut its recommendation on the
stock.  Embraer fell 2.2 percent to 16.16 reais at the close in Sao
Paulo, the biggest one-day slump since March 6. The benchmark
Bovespa index slipped 0.2 percent.  Goldman Sachs revised its rating on Embraer’s shares to
neutral from buy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jose Sergio Osse in Sao Paulo at 
 josse1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
